<doc>
  <member name="D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies how the layer contents should be prepared.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1.D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>Default layer behavior. A premultiplied layer target is pushed and its contents are cleared to transparent black.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1.D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1_INITIALIZE_FROM_BACKGROUND">
    <summary>
      <para>The layer is not cleared to transparent black.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1.D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1_IGNORE_ALPHA">
    <summary>
      <para>The layer is always created as ignore alpha. All content rendered into the layer will be treated as opaque.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1.D2D1_LAYER_OPTIONS1_FORCE_DWORD">
    <summary></summary>
  </member>
